Except for the magnesium complex, the Cdot and other complexes' calculated emission spectra show peaks at wavelengths between 400 and 413 nm. A fluorescence emission peak at the wavelength λEmi = 527 nm is ignited after the creation of this compound (Fig. 4
                        ). After absorption at the wavelength of λAbs = 395 nm, this complex really moves an excited electron from the valence layer (HOMO orbital) to the LUMO orbital without affecting the spin number, and emits in this peak at the wavelength of Emi = 611 nm. In Fig. 5
                        , this procedure is displayed. As can be observed, the complex's energy gap is a little smaller during emission than it is during absorption.
